I"ü<p>Horizontal stack card allows you to stack together multiple cards, so they always sit next to each other in the space of one column.</p>
<div class="config-vars">
  <h3><a class="title-link" name="configuration-variables" href="#configuration-variables"></a> Configuration Variables</h3>
  <dl class=''><dt><a class='title-link' name='type' href='#type'></a> type</dt><dd><p class='desc'><span class='type'>(<span class='string'>string</span>)</span><span class='required'>(Required)</span><span class='description'><p>horizontal-stack</p>
</span></p></dd><dt><a class='title-link' name='title' href='#title'></a> title</dt><dd><p class='desc'><span class='type'>(<span class='string'>string</span>)</span><span class='required'>(Optional)</span><span class='description'><p>Title of Stack</p>
</span></p></dd><dt><a class='title-link' name='cards' href='#cards'></a> cards</dt><dd><p class='desc'><span class='type'>(<span class='list'>list</span>)</span><span class='required'>(Required)</span><span class='description'><p>List of cards.</p>
</span></p></dd></dl>
</div>
<h2>Example</h2>
<pre><code class="language-yaml">type: horizontal-stack
title: Lights
cards:
  - type: picture-entity
    image: /local/bed_1.png
    entity: light.ceiling_lights
  - type: picture-entity
    image: /local/bed_2.png
    entity: light.bed_light
</code></pre>
